data.title: Oscar Wilde - The Importance of Being Earnest
data.meta_description: Oscar Wilde - The Importance of Being Earnest - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides background information on Oscar Wilde and summarizes his play "The Importance of Being Earnest". It includes a brief biography of Wilde noting he was an Irish playwright, novelist and poet in the late Victorian era known for his wit and celebrity. It also provides a high-level summary of the plot and characters of the play, which uses elements of farce and satire to skewer social norms of the time through the story of two friends who maintain fictitious personas.
